cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CY 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques to diagnose clinical conditions using electronic health records (EHR). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a novel model for this task, which involves iterative condensation of memory representations, making it relevant to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses a knowledge source from Wikipedia, which falls under the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques, which is relevant to the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with healthcare data, which can be considered as a subfield of cybernetics, making it relevant to the category of cs.CY (Computers and Society).
